“

Don't put all your eggs in one basket. Clinical trials will also be conducted to test the effectiveness of drugs such as Faviravir, chloroquine / hydroxychloroquine, and touzumab against new coronary pneumonia.

”

Since the outbreak of new crown pneumonia, the search for "special drugs" has never stopped, from cleats to Rudesivir, from Shuanghuanglian to various traditional Chinese medicine decoction.

As of February 18,2020, more than 100 clinical trials related to COVID-19 have been registered in China, the vast majority of which are clinical trials involving drug interventions. Apart from antiviral drug Welling, Lopinavir, Interferon and Glucocorticoid, which are included in the national version of the protocol, and what other drugs have the potential to treat NCP, as they are known?

According to the related reports and mechanism of efficacy, the anti-influenza virus drug Favipiravir, the anti-malaria drug chloroquine / hydroxychloroquine, and the autoimmune disease drug Tocilizumab may become the second possibility.

###Farvelavi "in the line of fire. "

After selection and screening, about 100 drugs were selected for in Vivo activity testing of COVID-19, said Zhang Xinmin, director of the Biotechnology Center of the Ministry of Science and technology, on February 15. On this basis, the research team focused on a small number of drugs, such as chloroquine phosphate, Lundinicivir (Ridicivir) , Favipiravir (Favelavir) , has carried out clinical trials, at present, some drugs have shown good clinical efficacy.

The next day, State Food and Drug Administration gave conditional approval for Haizheng Pharmaceutical's favelavir tablets to be marketed as a treatment for influenza related indications. FAVELAVIR is a broad-spectrum anti-influenza drug that acts as an RNA polymerase (RDRP) inhibitor, and neocoronavirus is also an RNA virus.

Developed by Japan's Joint-stock Company, Faviravir was launched in Japan in 2014 to treat both new and recurrent influenza, making it Japan's national strategic stockpile of drugs. In 2016, Haizheng Pharmaceutical signed an exclusive licensing agreement with Japan's joint-stock Company for the patent of the compound, and this approved favela tablet is the first domestic imitation product,

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It is worth noting that it took only about 10 days from the official acceptance of the drug registration of favela tablets to the completion of the approval process, it is reported that according to the new "Drug Control Act" in Article 26, "for the treatment of serious life-threatening diseases and no effective means of treatment of public health urgently needed drugs... May Be approved with conditions".

The conclusion of the approval of the drug registration of favelavir tablets also clearly mentioned that "in order to deal with the epidemic situation of new coronavirus pneumonia, in accordance with the "Drug Administration Law" , "Drug Registration Management Measures" ... In fact, Shanghai Zhengyao reported to the State Food and Drug Administration immediately after the outbreak of NCP and after the related discussions before the Spring Festival, according to interface news.

Haizheng pharmaceutical also filed an urgent report and obtained the clinical trial approval of favelavir tablets for the treatment of new coronary pneumonia. According to the Drug Administration Law, the measures for drug registration and the special examination and approval procedure for drugs, the company's announcement said, the product will be approved for clinical trials on an emergency basis after review and examination by a special expert group. The indication is COVID-19 pneumonia.

The newly revised "measures for the administration of drug registration" in 2019 added a chapter on "accelerating the listing and registration of drugs" , article 1 of the regulations stipulates that "in the event of a public health emergency and after the occurrence of a public health emergency, the State Administration May, in accordance with law, decide to grant special approval to the preventive and therapeutic drugs needed for public health emergencies. ".

The State Food and Drug Administration has opened a special review channel for new cap drugs and set up a special panel of experts to carry out preliminary reviews. At least 15 applications have been submitted for various categories, seven for consideration by the panel and three for State Food and Drug Administration.

It is reported that the registered clinical trial will be a national multicenter, randomized, double-blind, controlled clinical trial, with several hundred patients scheduled to receive either faviravir tablets or placebo under the current standard protocol, the contracted hospitals include the First Affiliated Hospital of the Medical College of Zhejiang University, hospitals in Wuhan, Shenzhen and other places.

In fact, some researchers have already launched an urgent clinical trial of the drug in patients with new coronary artery disease. In a clinical trial for COVID-19 pneumonia, which was initiated by the National Center for Clinical Research on infectious diseases and the third people's Hospital of Shenzhen (the Second Affiliated Hospital of Southern University of Science and technology) , the preliminary results of 80 cases from the test group and the Control Group showed that the treatment group had no obvious side effects, the side effects were obviously lower than that of the control group, the patients'compliance was better, and the antiviral effect after treatment was better than that of the control group.

Earlier, the drug registration document of favelavir tablets also mentioned the dissolution of Favelavir, and requested the completion of post-prandial bioequivalence studies, Haizheng pharmaceutical said in response to interface news, the pharmacodynamic comparison of Favelavir with the reference preparation was no problem, the fasting result was equivalent, the postprandial one was still being done, and the problem analysis of dissolution was completed.

###Chloroquine Phosphate / hydroxychloroquine sulfate

At a press conference on February 17th, sun Yanrong, deputy director of the Biological Center of the Ministry of Science and technology, once again mentioned that "in clinical practice, we have definitely seen the efficacy of [ chloroquine phosphate ] . No matter from a series of indexes, such as the rate of severe disease, the time when the fever subsided, the image of the lungs improved, the time when the virus nucleic acid turned negative and the rate of turning negative, as well as the course of disease, the Drug Group is superior to the Control Group through systematic and comprehensive research. " February 18, the People's Hospital of Wuhan University also said 20 patients improved significantly after taking hydroxychloroquine sulfate.

Chloroquine is also one of the few drugs that officials say they are certain to see a clinical benefit. In fact, the structure of hydroxychloroquine and chloroquine is similar, the mechanism of action is very similar, but the half-life of hydroxychloroquine is shorter than that of chloroquine, the metabolism is faster, the side effect is less, and the safety and tolerance of clinical use are improved obviously. The therapeutic effect of hydroxychloroquine is similar to that of chloroquine, so the clinical application of hydroxychloroquine is more extensive than that of chloroquine.

In fact, the two drugs are currently provided by Shanghai medicine, of which Shanghai medicine was the only one that was normally produced before chloroquine, and was mainly purchased by the World Health Organization before the outbreak of the new coronavirus pneumonia, according to the interface news, and collected by the CDC Strategic Reserve Health Commission.

However, as the therapeutic effect of chloroquine on new coronary pneumonia was disclosed, many domestic companies with the approval of chloroquine production also announced the resumption of production. Guangdong Province has not produced chloroquine for 20 years, but as of the morning of February 18, Guanghua Pharmaceutical, a holding subsidiary of the Guangyao Group, announced that it had produced the first batch of 500,000 tablets of chloroquine phosphate. Meanwhile, as of February 19, Guangdong Zhongsheng Pharmaceutical Industry has also completed the production of 198,000 tablets of chloroquine phosphate.

On hydroxychloroquine, only the original research and import Sanofi and Shanghai Pharmaceutical two have production approval, Shanghai Pharmaceutical 2019 half-yearly report showed that hydroxychloroquine (fenelop) domestic market share of 76.67% . According to the literature, the anti-SARS and Mers activities of hydroxychloroquine were similar to that of chloroquine.

However, the mechanism of chloroquine in the treatment of NCP is still unclear. A combination of literature and reports may include the following:

* Viruses: inhibit several pH-dependent steps of viral replication, including coronaviruses, by increasing the intracellular Ph, or by affecting the activation of mitogen-activated protein kinase and extracellular signal-regulated Kinase Erk, inhibition of the shedding andor Posttranslational modification of newly synthesized proteins, thereby inhibiting coronavirus infection and replication.
* IMMUNOMODULATION: By increasing the PH value of the CYTOPLASM, the amount of Antigen Polypeptide on the cell surface is reduced, and the processing of Antigen is blocked.
* Inflammation: hydroxychloroquine sulfate is weakly alkaline and increases the Ph of lysosomes, thus inhibiting the production of Proinflammatory cytokine (TNF-, ifn-, IL-2 and IL-4) .

ANTIVIRAL: Inhibition of several pH-dependent steps of viral replication, including coronaviruses, by increasing the intracellular Ph, or by affecting the activation of mitogen-activated protein kinase and extracellular signal-regulated Kinase Erk, inhibition of the shedding andor Posttranslational modification of newly synthesized proteins, thereby inhibiting coronavirus infection and replication.

IMMUNOMODULATION: by making the intracellular Ph value rise, reduce the cell surface antigen polypeptide quantity, prevent the antigen processing.

ANTI-INFLAMMATORY: hydroxychloroquine sulfate is weakly alkaline and increases the Ph of lysosomes, thus inhibiting the production of Proinflammatory cytokine (TNF-, ifn-, IL-2 and IL-4) .

These mechanisms may be time-dependent, creating barriers to the entry and replication of new coronaviruses at different stages, and inhibiting cytokine storms.

In 2003, The Lancet infectious diseases published an article on the antiviral effect of chloroquine, suggesting that chloroquine can be used to treat SARS. It has also been suggested that chloroquine inhibits the production and release of Tumor necrosis factors and Interleukin 6, it also means that chloroquine may be able to inhibit the direct cause of death of many severe NCP patients —— A cytokine storm.

It is understood that at first, it was the scientific research units in Beijing that selected chloroquine in the process of screening available old drugs. The Ministry of Science and technology contacted Shanghai Pharmaceutical on January 29 for this purpose. Shanghai pharmaceutical subsidiary Zhongxi immediately transferred the entire stock of more than 25,000 boxes of chloroquine and overnight sent it to the Ministry of Science and Technology for research and testing.

Chloroquine also showed anti-neocoronavirus activity and therapeutic effect in the following in vitro studies and clinical trials. Because the molecular structure of hydroxychloroquine and chloroquine is very close, but the safety is much better, and the Mechanism of action and curative effect for the existing indications are similar, so hydroxychloroquine also quickly entered the researchers'vision.

In fact, even before the official public recognition of the efficacy of chloroquine / hydroxychloroquine, patients were self-administered and had positive results.

Zhihu user "Theozheng" on Zhihu recorded the engagement of his girlfriend's father nearly half a month to self-medication of hydroxychloroquine experience. The patient began to develop symptoms on January 24, followed by persistent fever and frequent dry cough over the next few days. Laboratory blood tests and CT results showed a high degree of suspicion of new coronary pneumonia, after the local hospital in Wuhan capacity can only be isolated at home.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Starting Feb. 5, the patient was treated with hydroxychloroquine, according to previous literature, and his condition became stable and improved. Blood tests and CT were positive on February 13, and the patient was completely off the drug on February 16. Three days before the withdrawal of the drug, his mental state and state were almost completely restored to normal. At present, the community cadres agreed to take home quarantine observation measures.

At present, the Shanghai Municipal Clinical Center for Public Health, the Ruijin Hospital affiliated to Shanghai Jiaotong University, the People's Hospital of Wuhan University, the Peking University First Hospital, the first hospital affiliated to the Chongqing Medical University and the Second Hospital have all launched clinical studies on the treatment of new coronavirus pneumonia with hydroxychloroquine, the subjects included mild to moderate, severe, and critically ill patients.

###If tozumab can slow a deadly cytokine storm

One thing that has been speculated about the mechanism of chloroquine in the treatment of Tumor necrosis factors pneumonia is that it inhibits the production and release of Tumor necrosis factors and several cytokines.

According to previous reports in the domestic media and the Lancet, many patients with severe new coronary pneumonia will suddenly develop an inflammatory storm in the body, namely Cytokine Release Syndrome, also known as CYTOKINE storm, this can lead to a rapid deterioration of the patient's condition in a short period of time.

In short, after the new coronavirus invades the body, the body's self-immune switch is turned on and the virus-fighting immune cells begin to release various cytokines to stimulate more immune cells to participate in the immune system, these stimulated immune cells also continue to release more cytokines.

But in infections such as those caused by SARS and Zaire Ebolavirus, massive and rapid cytokine production can lead to cytokine storms that eventually lead to attacks on the body's own immune system, it is like a "suicide attack" against the virus, leading to low blood pressure, blood clots, heart, lung, liver and kidney failure and other important organ failure and Acute respiratory distress syndrome, life-threatening.

"The Lancet" published on January 25 by Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, china-japan Friendship Hospital, Peking Union Medical College, Beijing Temple of Earth Hospital, Wuhan Tongji Hospital, Wuhan Central Hospital, Wuhan University Zhongnan Hospital, Peking University First Hospital, Peking University People's Hospital and other experts co-authored "2019 Wuhan COVID-19 clinical characteristics" also mentioned:

"The initial plasma concentrations of IL1B, Il1ra, IL7, IL8, IL9, IL10, basic FGF, GCSF, GMCSF, IFN, IP10, MCP1, MIP1A, MIP1B, PDGF, TNF and VEGF in ICU and non-ICU patients were all higher than those in healthy adults. Plasma levels of IL5, IL12p70, IL15, Eosinophil granulocyte and Rantes were similar in healthy adults and patients infected with 2019-nCoV. Further comparisons between ICU and non-ICU patients showed that plasma concentrations of IL2, IL7, IL10, GCSF, IP10, MCP1, MIP1A and TNF were higher in Icu than in non-ICU patients."

In ICU patients and non-ICU patients, there was a significant increase in cytokines, some of which were higher in ICU patients.

According to the website of China Clinical Trial Registration Center, a multicenter, randomized controlled clinical trial on the efficacy and safety of Tuzumab in COVID-19 pneumonia COVID-19, initiated by the First Affiliated Hospital of the University of Science and Technology of China (Anhui Provincial Hospital) , has been registered for appointment. Objective to evaluate the efficacy and safety of Tozumab in the treatment of common type of NCP and severe type of NCP.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tuzumab (Yamiluo) is an interleukin-6(IL-6 antagonist, mainly used in rheumatoid arthritis and other autoimmune diseases, with the role of inhibiting the immune system. Notably, when the world's first CAR-T therapy was approved in the United States in 2017, Touzumab was also approved for the treatment of CAR-T associated Severe Cytokine Release Syndrome. In other words, Tozumab has actually proven its ability to treat cytokine storms.

But this does not mean that Tuzumab will necessarily cure the cytokine storm caused by new pneumonia.

According to the findings of the January 25 Lancet study, IL-6 was not the main cytokine that increased in patients with NCP, this means that the pathogenesis of Cytokine Elevation Syndrome may not be the same for different ETIOLOGIES, and it may not be possible to treat the disease with Tozumab. However, the results of 27 cytokines were provided in the paper supplement, and there were several severe patients with extremely significant increases in IL-6, such patients are more likely to be effective with Tozumab. The First Affiliated Hospital of the University of Science and Technology of China (Anhui Provincial Hospital) also limited the inclusion of patients with elevated IL-6, should also be considered the underlying mechanism and risk.

But Kornan also said that in the Cytokine Release Syndrome mechanism, the IL-6 position is relatively core, inhibited IL-6 other should be stable.

Previous studies on Tumor therapy-induced Cytokine Release Syndrome have shown that three cytokines, IL-6, IL-10 and Interferon (IFN -) , play an important role in the pathogenesis.

He also cautioned that the first item in the "Do's and don'ts" section of Tozumab's drug description, which is labeled "black box warning" by the FDA, was a severe infection following immunosuppression, this means that the regulator does not recommend the use of immunosuppressive drug in combination with other drugs, requiring that in the event of a serious infection, the use of Tuzumab be stopped immediately. According to its understanding, many doctors in Wuhan area have not prescribed Tozumab, lack of clinical experience is also a practical problem.

According to the supplemental data, tumor necrosis factor (TNF) is also a worthwhile target for a cytokine storm in critically ill patients with NCP, according to Conan analysis. The target is a collection of well known drugs, including Adamumab, SIPP, infliximab and so on.

Still, the evidence and rigour of modern medicine are a reminder that every drug, no matter what, should be tested in rigorous clinical trials, even as the disease rages and specific drugs are desperately needed, make sure it's safe and effective.
